* Story to be updated Durban - ANC PR councillor and former ANC Youth League leader Sindiso Magaqa who was shot in July, along with two other councillors, has succumbed to his injuries. At the time  ANC KwaZulu-Natal provincial spokesperson Mdumiseni Ntuli said that Magaqa, ward 11 councillor Nonsikelelo Mafa and ward 16 councillor Jabu Mzizi were shot while they were at a local shop together. The trio were at a general dealer in ward 11, said Ntuli, when the shootings took place.
 
“They were parked outside a general dealer when a red BMW came, people got out and opened fire on them and drove off,” he said. ANA and IOL